    "f5332588-ee9e-4cb8-b588-7497ef23f2f0": {
      "type": "rich-text",
      "blocks": {
        "c1f503b4-5a46-4990-8e45-753347835b3c": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "About this role",
            "heading_size": "h1"
          }
        },
        "template--18850231484751__f5332588-ee9e-4cb8-b588-7497ef23f2f0-16824067253affbd63-1": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>In the grand scheme of things, Loop is pretty young. But each day we’re getting bigger and bolder, and we’re consistently bringing <strong>new<\/strong> <strong>products<\/strong> to the market and working away on new development projects.<br\/>And with our ambitions to be the <strong>leader<\/strong> in <strong>enhanced<\/strong> <strong>hearing<\/strong> and to give people control over how they hear life, in style and confidence, we need new, exciting people to join our team – people like you.<\/p><p>You might wonder: ‘yeah but what’s in it for the engineers?’<\/p><p>Well, where shall we begin… We are working on different projects in our <strong>passive<\/strong> <strong>sound<\/strong> control products.<br\/>You can think about acoustic foams, membranes, meshes, acoustic channels, Helmholtz absorbers, and so much more!<\/p><p>Next to that, we’re working on <strong>active<\/strong> <strong>sound<\/strong> control products.<br\/>You can start dreaming about the possibilities we can create when we add electronics to our products. Maybe even active noise control?<br\/>But that’s just the beginning. Imagine what we can do with personalized sound experience based on machine learning, health sensing or AI for sound control in everyday live. We could go on about it for a paragraph or two but you’re a creative engineer who thinks big, so you’ll figure it out yourself right? ;)<\/p>",
            "description_padding": 32
          }
        },
        "82ff3a37-8cad-430f-95db-9cbdeeef6ec9": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Testing, testing, one two",
            "heading_size": "h1"
          }
        },
        "32a98dbe-f634-469b-8904-0f5d2149e699": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>You’ve got plenty of <strong>experience<\/strong> as embedded hardware and\/or software engineer, or electronics engineer.<br\/>So, when asked, you can easily give some examples of electronic embedded system developments for consumer or electronic goods you worked on.<br\/>Plus, that degree in <strong>electronical \/ electromechanical<\/strong> <strong>engineering<\/strong>, industrial engineering, or another relevant field certainly helps.<\/p><p>Due to your practical hands-on mentality, developing proof of concepts and <strong>breadboards<\/strong> is what gives you energy, together with thoroughly <strong>inspecting<\/strong> <strong>and<\/strong> <strong>testing<\/strong> our products before they’re launched.<br\/>You put them through the wringer at every stage of the product development process and identify any <strong>potential<\/strong> <strong>issues<\/strong> and <strong>recommend<\/strong> <strong>improvements<\/strong> – because you’re smart like that.<\/p><p>You’ve got a problem-solving mindset, a <strong>hands-on attitude<\/strong> to get things done, high quality standards, and even higher safety standards.<br\/>And you share these standards with our product development and advanced engineering teams who you work closely with every day – plus Tom, our senior system engineer who leads the advanced engineering team.<\/p>",
            "description_padding": 32
          }
        },
        "d99470d8-e10d-499d-af5b-a48e327e428f": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Your excellence rings clear",
            "heading_size": "h1"
          }
        },
        "82e61271-9c1d-4bd4-aee8-3f6ae305e621": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>We can count on you for the specifications, concept validation and technical follow-up of the electronic systems, both for hardware and software.<br\/>For this, you’d be happy to take the ownership by supporting the hardware and software developments from proof of concept, to prototype, up to validated, market-ready electronic systems.<\/p>",
            "description_padding": 32
          }
        }
      },
