    "8f7b78d2-26a9-4b37-8ed4-c67b5c20f4de": {
      "type": "rich-text",
      "blocks": {
        "30fd07cb-39d2-4f2e-af41-5c15b79ef649": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "You vibe with our R&amp;D",
            "heading_size": "h1"
          }
        },
        "5ccb5a5c-f043-4ef1-82fc-baecc4f5822a": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Our team loves how effectively you support them. Especially when you support and contribute to <strong>the R&D team<\/strong> on our future innovative products.<br\/>You're a <strong>PCB design wizard<\/strong>, you've got experience with <strong>battery<\/strong> management, and a solid knowledge of <strong>coding<\/strong> – you’re basically a bit of a know-it-all, but we like that.<br\/>You know that each project will vary in size – but that’s OK because you’re <strong>passionate<\/strong> about what you do. And with our constant support and flexibility, and a healthy <strong>R&D budget<\/strong>, you have everything you need to succeed.<\/p><p>Sounding good? Now before we shake hands, there are a couple of non-negotiable requirements that we have:<\/p><ul><li>You’re confident, have strong presentation skills – both written and verbal – and you’re fluent in <strong>English<\/strong>. If you speak any other languages then that would be pretty cool too.<\/li><li>You’re located near and willing to work in our <strong>Antwerp<\/strong> office on a weekly basis. It’s where our product development and advanced engineering team is based. And since you'll be working with a physical product, we’d obviously need you to be there.<\/li><li>You have a degree in Engineering.<\/li><li>You have experience in consumer goods, preferably electronics products.<\/li><li>You have a sound knowledge of PCB design.<\/li><\/ul>",
            "description_padding": 32
          }
        },
